            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p><strong>Meanwhile</strong>, peel and finely slice the red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">(s)</span></p>\r\n<p><strong>Heat</strong> a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">(2 tbsp)</span> vegetable oil over a medium-high heat</p>\r\n<p><strong>Once</strong> hot, add the onion with a big pinch of both salt and sugar (use brown sugar if you have it!)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cook</strong> for 4 min or until slightly softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
